<TITLE> Fugitive BDR man caught, sent to jail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rangpur, June 28 (bdnews24.com)Fugitive BDR soldier Noor Hossain and his elder brother Mozammel Haque Babu were sent to jail on Sunday. RAB arrested Hossain, 33, at Darshana in connection with the case filed after the Feb 25-26 mutiny in the border guards' Peelkhana headquarters in Dhaka. Kotwali police took them to the court of magistrate Shyam Shundor Roy who ordered them into Rangpur central jail. Officer in charge of Kotwali Police Station Abdur Rashid told the reporters the would be taken to Dhaka. Rangpur RAB officer major Alamgir said they were the inhabitants of Santoshpur at Sandwip in Chittagong. Noor was on the list of the 78 fugitive BDR soldiers, Alamgir said. He was directly involved with the killing of the army officers deputed to BDR, hiding the bodies and looting, the RAB officer claimed. RAB suspected that the fugitive had planned to escape to India through Dinajpur's Hili border. RAB handed them over to Kotwali police station Sunday morning. bdnews24.c
